DefaultChoiceDisplayText.SourceString: Sing the bard's song of rememberance.
DefaultChoiceDisplayText.LocalizedString: Sing the bard's song of rememberance.

Message.SourceString: This song was written for you... In memory of you. Yet the lump in my throat is so great, I cannot sound the words.
Message.LocalizedString: This song was written for you... In memory of you. Yet the lump in my throat is so great, I cannot sound the words.

Message.SourceString: I'm sorry, Meya, even now I cannot say goodbye. So let me just say the words that mean the most.
Message.LocalizedString: I'm sorry, Meya, even now I cannot say goodbye. So let me just say the words that mean the most.

Message.SourceString: This song was written for you... In memory of you. Yet the lump in my throat is so great, I cannot sound the words.
Message.LocalizedString: This song was written for you... In memory of you. Yet the lump in my throat is so great, I cannot sound the words.

Message.SourceString: I laid your bones to rest beneath this tree, far from our home. I felt you deserved one last adventure, stretched out across our little world.
Message.LocalizedString: I laid your bones to rest beneath this tree, far from our home. I felt you deserved one last adventure, stretched out across our little world.

Message.SourceString: My journey continues eastward, following the blue in a sea made from waves of colourful dancing leaves. Saying my farewell, each footstep at a time.
Message.LocalizedString: My journey continues eastward, following the blue in a sea made from waves of colourful dancing leaves. Saying my farewell, each footstep at a time.

Message.SourceString: You don't have enough space for the crystal seed to grow into the bow. You will need to make some room before it can do so.
Message.LocalizedString: You don't have enough space for the crystal seed to grow into the bow. You will need to make some room before it can do so.

Message.SourceString: Dw i'n dy garu di'n fawr.
Message.LocalizedString: Dw i'n dy garu di'n fawr.

Message.SourceString:
Y baradwys

Our world of adventure and excitement, held between four small walls.
Message.LocalizedString:
Y baradwys

Our world of adventure and excitement, held between four small walls.

Message.SourceString: We shared a meal. I told stories and you listened in a way that no one has ever listened before. All of you, every part of your being, focused on my words. I think I loved you even then, though it would be years before I realised it.
Message.LocalizedString: We shared a meal. I told stories and you listened in a way that no one has ever listened before. All of you, every part of your being, focused on my words. I think I loved you even then, though it would be years before I realised it.

Message.SourceString:
Trefn elitaidd rhyfelwyr affwysol   

Leaving me behind, so that you could save us all.
Message.LocalizedString:
Trefn elitaidd rhyfelwyr affwysol   

Leaving me behind, so that you could save us all.

Message.SourceString:
Er mwyn tynged Gilinor. Oh Gielinor  Maen daith un ffordd i fewn ir affwys, i Gilinor   

Thats why you left me. Not the ravage of time. Not the cruelty of fire-red hair turning the silver-grey of burnt-out ash. You had a mission, a journey, to take the fight into the abyss.
Message.LocalizedString:
Er mwyn tynged Gilinor. Oh Gielinor  Maen daith un ffordd i fewn ir affwys, i Gilinor   

Thats why you left me. Not the ravage of time. Not the cruelty of fire-red hair turning the silver-grey of burnt-out ash. You had a mission, a journey, to take the fight into the abyss.

Message.SourceString: I laid your bones to rest beneath this tree, far from our home. I felt you deserved one last adventure, stretched out across our little world.
Message.LocalizedString: I laid your bones to rest beneath this tree, far from our home. I felt you deserved one last adventure, stretched out across our little world.

Message.SourceString: Yet, even as time left its wounds in your skin, you were still the most beautiful creature in all of Gielinor.
Message.LocalizedString: Yet, even as time left its wounds in your skin, you were still the most beautiful creature in all of Gielinor.

Message.SourceString: This view feels so different without you by my side. The angle is strange, because my shoulder isnt weighed by your head as you lean on me and sigh softly. A hundred years without you, and yet this view still feels wrong.
Message.LocalizedString: This view feels so different without you by my side. The angle is strange, because my shoulder isnt weighed by your head as you lean on me and sigh softly. A hundred years without you, and yet this view still feels wrong.

Message.SourceString:
Creaduriaid. Adfeilion.   

Monsters and desolation, everywhere we looked. Yet somehow we made a home, a ramshackle house of nonsense, that became my paradise.
Message.LocalizedString:
Creaduriaid. Adfeilion.   

Monsters and desolation, everywhere we looked. Yet somehow we made a home, a ramshackle house of nonsense, that became my paradise.

Message.SourceString:
Marhog Gwagle! I Gielinor! 
Marchog Gwagle! Marchog! I Gielinor!   

A brave warrior, defender of the world. Defeated by a tree.
Message.LocalizedString:
Marhog Gwagle! I Gielinor! 
Marchog Gwagle! Marchog! I Gielinor!   

A brave warrior, defender of the world. Defeated by a tree.

Message.SourceString: Not you though. I remember sitting alone in the forests, wolves circling me, and then a loud crash, boisterous laughter and a mad-woman in leaf-covered armour falls out of a tree and says hello.
Message.LocalizedString: Not you though. I remember sitting alone in the forests, wolves circling me, and then a loud crash, boisterous laughter and a mad-woman in leaf-covered armour falls out of a tree and says hello.

Message.SourceString:
Y byd dirdro. Tir llygredig   

Ghornfell is a harsh place, filled with dangers. The land itself is twisted, poison to the east and storms to the west. Overhead the dread Velgar circles, laughing at the destruction hes wrought.
Message.LocalizedString:
Y byd dirdro. Tir llygredig   

Ghornfell is a harsh place, filled with dangers. The land itself is twisted, poison to the east and storms to the west. Overhead the dread Velgar circles, laughing at the destruction hes wrought.

Message.SourceString: Im still not sure why we chose this land. Brynmoor was much calmer.
Message.LocalizedString: Im still not sure why we chose this land. Brynmoor was much calmer.

Message.SourceString: We found a home here, together, the Wild Knight and her strange elf bard. We took the logs from the forests, and the stone from the mountains floor, so that we might craft a little place where we could escape together.
Message.LocalizedString: We found a home here, together, the Wild Knight and her strange elf bard. We took the logs from the forests, and the stone from the mountains floor, so that we might craft a little place where we could escape together.

Message.SourceString:
Y pyrth hynaf,  
ar goll   

Those elder gates, stealing more of you from me.
Message.LocalizedString:
Y pyrth hynaf,  
ar goll   

Those elder gates, stealing more of you from me.

Message.SourceString: Every time you stepped out the door, it was as if time took some of you from me. In barely a handful of years your limbs stiffened, you fire-red hair turned grey and you lost some of the agility you had been so proud of.
Message.LocalizedString: Every time you stepped out the door, it was as if time took some of you from me. In barely a handful of years your limbs stiffened, you fire-red hair turned grey and you lost some of the agility you had been so proud of.

Message.SourceString: To an elf time is a fickle thing, we age so much slower that time passes almost without meaning. A year to us is a heartbeat, a decade is nothing but a brief rest, a century can be as easily forgotten as any other time. But not for you.
Message.LocalizedString: To an elf time is a fickle thing, we age so much slower that time passes almost without meaning. A year to us is a heartbeat, a decade is nothing but a brief rest, a century can be as easily forgotten as any other time. But not for you.

Message.SourceString: You were Guthixs sword, his piercing light against the darkness. Thats why you left me. Not because of time. Not because you were never coming back. But because you needed to save us all from the monsters in the night.
Message.LocalizedString: You were Guthixs sword, his piercing light against the darkness. Thats why you left me. Not because of time. Not because you were never coming back. But because you needed to save us all from the monsters in the night.

Message.SourceString:
Clwych curor drymiau rhyfel,  A ffanffer Guthix yn canu   

I imagined your war-song as you lead your Wild Knights into battle.
Message.LocalizedString:
Clwych curor drymiau rhyfel,  A ffanffer Guthix yn canu   

I imagined your war-song as you lead your Wild Knights into battle.

Message.SourceString:
Cleddyf guthix ydym ni  
Ni yw'r golau treiddgar  
Yr ydm yma
I drechu pob cysgod. I Gielinor!
Message.LocalizedString:
Cleddyf guthix ydym ni  
Ni yw'r golau treiddgar  
Yr ydm yma
I drechu pob cysgod. I Gielinor!

Message.SourceString: You didnt die, you just went off to battle. Thats how I could brave the years. In the songs I wrote about you, you were off to war, fighting for Guthix against all the evils in creation.
Message.LocalizedString: You didnt die, you just went off to battle. Thats how I could brave the years. In the songs I wrote about you, you were off to war, fighting for Guthix against all the evils in creation.

Message.SourceString: A shield against a shadowy emptiness. My void knight.
Message.LocalizedString: A shield against a shadowy emptiness. My void knight.

Message.SourceString: Wanderlust overcame reason and I journeyed across the ocean to find myself. Ashenfall is no place for an elf. There is no crystal, save what I brought with me, and the humans here distrust all outsiders. Not without reason.
Message.LocalizedString: Wanderlust overcame reason and I journeyed across the ocean to find myself. Ashenfall is no place for an elf. There is no crystal, save what I brought with me, and the humans here distrust all outsiders. Not without reason.

Message.SourceString: So I wrote this song to conjure up the essence of you, rather than the fact. A bards prerogative, evoke the feelings you left in others, rather than record your daily toils.
Message.LocalizedString: So I wrote this song to conjure up the essence of you, rather than the fact. A bards prerogative, evoke the feelings you left in others, rather than record your daily toils.

Message.SourceString:
Gadael pob peth ar l    

Leaving everything behind, I thought only I did that.
Message.LocalizedString:
Gadael pob peth ar l    

Leaving everything behind, I thought only I did that.

Message.SourceString: I never liked your story. Child of a farmer, given over to the Wild Knights, because of the fire in your eyes. It felt as if you were owed a greater story, one that could deliver even a fraction of your courage.
Message.LocalizedString: I never liked your story. Child of a farmer, given over to the Wild Knights, because of the fire in your eyes. It felt as if you were owed a greater story, one that could deliver even a fraction of your courage.

Message.SourceString: I'm sorry, Meya, even now I cannot say goodbye. So let me just say the words that mean the most.
Message.LocalizedString: I'm sorry, Meya, even now I cannot say goodbye. So let me just say the words that mean the most.

Message.SourceString: Dw i'n dy garu di'n fawr.
Message.LocalizedString: Dw i'n dy garu di'n fawr.

Message.SourceString: As the last words leave your lips, the seed shivers and shudders to the song. It twists, stretches and transforms into a bow of glittering crystal.
Message.LocalizedString: As the last words leave your lips, the seed shivers and shudders to the song. It twists, stretches and transforms into a bow of glittering crystal.

Message.SourceString: You find a crystal in the shape of a seed. The memorial stone changes as you hold the crystal up, revealing text in elvish.
Message.LocalizedString: You find a crystal in the shape of a seed. The memorial stone changes as you hold the crystal up, revealing text in elvish.

Message.SourceString: Its time for me to leave this place. To close this chapter on our memories and to start a life without you. I need to find myself again, without your shadow smiling out of the corner of my eye.
Message.LocalizedString: Its time for me to leave this place. To close this chapter on our memories and to start a life without you. I need to find myself again, without your shadow smiling out of the corner of my eye.

Message.SourceString: I wrote a song about you, about the time we spent together. Its a technique of my people, turning music into craft. I will play the pieces of it, as I take this goodbye walk.
Message.LocalizedString: I wrote a song about you, about the time we spent together. Its a technique of my people, turning music into craft. I will play the pieces of it, as I take this goodbye walk.

Message.SourceString: I will start at our tree, in the east. Do you see it, down there, framed perfectly in this spot? A single point of brilliant blue, in an ocean of fiery red. An outsider, just like I was, until I met you.
Message.LocalizedString: I will start at our tree, in the east. Do you see it, down there, framed perfectly in this spot? A single point of brilliant blue, in an ocean of fiery red. An outsider, just like I was, until I met you.
